interactions.flavorLineOne: "His Imperial Majest sends his regards. And a just reward for a truuuuuuuue champion_%$&*%%" â€”Benedict 99-40
Benedict sweeps the floor as you offer him the gift. He reaches to take it and says through a buzz of static, "All glory to the Emperor."
Emperor Calus was delighted to have you aboard the Leviathan again. You are always welcome at his table.

headerDisplayProperties.description: x#4(_ This maintenance frame is *amp;_ eager to assist you with #*amp; TREASURES FROM THE EMPEROR.  x#9(_
headerDisplayProperties.name: Benedict 99-40

interactions.flavorLineOne:
The "Crown of Sorrow" raid is now active.

One of the Emperor's Loyalists believed he could control an Ascendant artifact. Now the Hive control him. Put Gahlran, the Sorrow-Bearer out of his misery and reclaim the Crown.

You present Gahlran's helmet to the frame.

Calus speaks through it, as ever. He alludes vaguely to something that he saw out at the edge of the universe during his exile, something that he calls "the truth of the universe."

You'll need to cultivate a greater sense of appreciation for such truths. Perhaps if you spend more time with the Emperor, you'll learn more.
Calus is interested by your alliance with the Awoken of the Reef. Should the opportunity arise, he wants you to "put in a good word" for him.

Benedict stops sweeping and turns to face you. "His Highness sends his good wishes for you at this celebrated time of year," he says. "The Great Emperor rejoices in the overwhelming inevitability of death and is pleased that the Guardian-tribe does the same."

He turns and continues to sweep. "Feast and be merry in the Emperor's name."
Emperor Calus was delighted to have you aboard the Leviathan again. You are always welcome at his table.

headerDisplayProperties.description: x#4(_ This maintenance frame is *amp;_ eager to assist you with #*amp; TREASURES FROM THE EMPEROR.  x#9(_
headerDisplayProperties.name: Benedict 99-40

interactions.flavorLineOne: "### Vzzzzt. Imperial Majesty â€¦ threat detected. Weaponsmith â€¦ continuing threat. Remove #&&_obstacle now. Reap the reward from his Highness." â€”Benedict 99-40
"You have not yettttt faced the _#*&% greatest challenge his Highness has to offer." â€”Benedict 99-40
"vvvwwwweell done. His Royal Highness bids you show_$%& your loyalty. Use his gift to end the traitorzzzzzz." â€”Benedict 99-40
"kkkkkkzk still much to prove to his Highness. Return to the Leviathan. Seek glory in his nammmme." â€”Benedict 99-40

As Calus speaks through Werner 99-40's stolen body, the frame offers you a fragmented Chalice.

Calus invites you to restore the Chalice, a symbol of power for his Shadowsâ€”elite Imperial assassins, the epitome of their respective alien races.

Calus is pleased by your swift progress, but the potential of the Chalice of Opulence far exceeds your efforts today.

Only by entering Calus's Menagerie on the Leviathan will you begin to unlock its true abilities.

As Benedict's core processes seem to hitch and jitter, a commanding presence overtakes the poor frame. A different voice booms through Benedict's speakers.

Emperor Calus, the hedonistic ruler of the Leviathan, has been watching you for some time. He invites you to Nessus, offering riches.

Nothing suspicious about that!

As Benedict's core processes seem to hitch and jitter, a commanding presence overtakes the poor frame. A different voice booms through Benedict's speakers.

Emperor Calus, the hedonistic ruler of the Leviathan, has been watching you for some time. He invites you to Nessus, offering riches.

Nothing suspicious about that!
"Scanning Tower inventory listsâ€¦ Seems like another maintenance frame went on the fritz and disappeared from the Hangar a day or two ago." â€”Ghost
Your reputation in Calus's court precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
Complete the "Leviathan" raid and challenges to obtain Emperor Calus tokens and earn rewards from Benedict 99-40.
Show Benedict 99-40 proof of Emperor Calus's favor.

interactions.flavorLineOne: The Visage of Calus

headerDisplayProperties.description: Exchange a Boon for an increased discount on all tributes.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Opulence

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Your many successes in Calus's Menagerie have more than demonstrated that you are worthy of a new title: Shadow of Earth.

Tread carefully. All of Calus's other Shadows succumbed to inglorious ends.

Via remote mechanism, Calus presents you with your first tribute.

"Take this," he says. "Find a suitable place of honor for it, little Guardian. And then let me see you fill this whole hall until it overflows with the evidence of your golden strength."
As you place your gift at the golden statue's feet, it swivels its head to look at you and opens its mouth. The Emperor laughs, deep and delighted.

Speaking through his robotic double, Calus tells you that Gahlran's so-called Crown of Sorrow had a very peculiar effect on the Leviathanâ€”it briefly split the seams of reality, allowing access to an altered plane of reality that Calus believes you're quite familiar with.

Calus's men ventured in and found the frame of a cursed gun. Since then, the gun's incorporeal essence has tormented the Leviathan's upper decks and eluded Calus's grasp.

Perhaps you'll have better luck than the Cabal.

Calus has a deep and abiding admiration for your tenacity and endurance. As a small token of his affection, he has built this Tribute Hall for you to fill with trophies.

Of course, you'll have to earn those trophiesâ€¦

interactions.flavorLineOne:
As you approach the Umbral Decoder, Drifter's pre-recorded voice plays from its tinny speakers.

"Whoa, there! If you're hearin' this, you're touchin' my machines in the wrong order! There'll be plenty of time for decoding later, but now you gotta check out the Recaster!"

You look over at the Drifter, who can barely contain his joy. "Gotcha, Hero!" he manages to say before dissolving into peals of laughter.

The branch gifted to you by the Pyramid has gorged on paracausal power and been bound to you through Eris's repurposing of SavathÃ»n's twisted rituals. Contained within an engram structure, the branch is ready to be forged within the Umbral Decoder. As you grip it, a cold emptiness stings your fingers briefly before subsiding, barely noticed. It is time for this gift to find its final shape.
Decode Umbral Engrams into weapons and armor. Drifter swears this device is perfectly safe to use.
